article.headline: S. Dakota St. 65, Montana St. 62
article.story: BROOKINGS, S.D. (AP) -- South Dakota State came from behind in the second half to beat Montana State 65-62 behind Matt Cadwell's 23 points on Friday. Cadwell was one of three players in double figures for the Jackrabbits (4-10). Kai Williams added 17 points and seven rebounds and Garrett Callahan chipped in 13 points. SDSU trailed 36-30 at halftime despite shooting 48 percent in the first half The Bobcats (3-10) were 3-for-14 from inside the arc, but they went 9-for-13 from 3-point range in the first half to take the lead. But they made just four more 3-pointers in the second half and shot only 37 percent overall. Branden Johnson had four 3-pointers and 16 points for MSU. Nick Dissly added three 3-pointers and 15 points. He also had seven rebounds. SDSU went 14-for-27 from the free throw line, while the Bobcats made five of eight attempts. MSU had 19 turnovers.
